{"lemma":"رُوعِ","slug":"رُوعِ","root":"ر.#.ع","root_slug":"ر-_-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-_-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"رُوعِ","root":"روع","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n17079","n17080","n17081","n17082"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%B9%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to terrify, to scare, to frighten, to terrorize, to intimidate"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of رَاعَ (rāʕa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bosom, heart, animus, the place where fear is felt"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"amazing beauty, terrific fairness"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n17079","headword_ar":"رَوْعٌ","root":"rwE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[see 1, of which it is an inf. n. ―         -b2- ]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fright,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fear;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawEN","text_ar":"رَوعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[accord. to some, but this seems to be little known]. (TA.) Hence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aforaxa rawoEuhu","text_ar":"اَفْرَخَ رَوْعُهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His fright,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fear, departed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) Az says, All the lexicologists whom I have met say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aforaxa rawoEuhu","text_ar":"اَفْرَخَ رَوْعُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"r","text_ar":"ر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rwEh","text_ar":"روعه"},{"kind":"text","text":"], except El-Mundhiree, who informs me that AHeyth used to say, It is only ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Afrx rawoEuka","text_ar":"افرخ رَوْعُكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm. (TA.) Accord. to different relations of a trad., you say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aforaxa ruwEuka","text_ar":"اَفْرَخَ رُوعُكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fright,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fear, hath departed from thy heart;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may fright,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fear, depart from thy heart;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) thus expl. by AHeyth; (TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Afrx rawoEuka","text_ar":"افرخ رَوْعُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h; or this latter, only, is the right, and means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what thou fearest hath quitted thee, and departed from thee, and become removed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may what thou fearest quit thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; as though it were taken from the young bird's going forth from the egg, (K, TA,) and the darkness' becoming removed from it; thus expl. by Aboo-Ahmad El-Hasan Ibn-' Abd-Allah Ibn-Sa'eed El-' Askeree; and AO says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Afrx rwEk","text_ar":"افرخ روعك"},{"kind":"text","text":"[thus in the TA, without any syll. signs,] means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"let thy fright,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fear, depart,"},{"kind":"text","text":"for the case is not as thou fearest it to be. (TA.) It is also said, in a trad. of Mo'áwiyeh, that he wrote in a letter to Ziyád, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liyuforixo ruwEuka","text_ar":"لِيُفْرِخْ رُوعُكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm; (K, TA;) but the opinion commonly obtaining with the leading lexicologists is, that it is with fet-h; except AHeyth, who relates it thus, with damm; (TA;) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dismiss thou the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawoE","text_ar":"رَوْع"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from thy"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruwE","text_ar":"رُوع"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the fright,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fear, from thy heart:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) for you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aforaxati AlbayoDapu","text_ar":"اَفْرَخَتِ البَيْضَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"when the young bird quits the egg; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawoE","text_ar":"رَوْع"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fright,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"which does not depart from itself, but from its place, which is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruwE","text_ar":"رُوع"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm; (AHeyth, K;) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawoE","text_ar":"رَوْع"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruwE","text_ar":"رُوع"},{"kind":"text","text":"being like the young bird in the egg: in like manner also one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aforaxa fuw^aAdu Alr~ajuli","text_ar":"اَفْرَخَ فُوَادُ الرَّجُلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"when a man's fright, or fear, departs: but Dhu-r-Rummeh, though knowing the meaning, has made an inversion, saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"qado A^aforaxato Eano ruwEihi Alkurabu"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qado A^aforaxa Eani Alkurabi ruwEuhu","text_ar":"قَدْ اَفْرَخَ عَنِ الكُرَبِ رُوعُهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His heart had freed itself from griefs"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (AHeyth, TA.) AHeyth adds, (TA,) one also says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eani AlA^amori","text_ar":"عَنِ الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aforixa ruwEaka","text_ar":"اَفْرِخَ رُوعَكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY AlA^amori","text_ar":"عَلَى الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [accord. to different copies of the K, the latter being the reading in the TA, but the former probably the right,] meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Free thy heart from the affair;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be thou tranquil, and without fear."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) Az observes, What AHeyth says is clear; but I am averse from it because of his being alone in his saying; though sometimes later authorities correct things in which the earlier have erred; therefore the correctness of AHeyth may not be [absolutely] denied in this matter, seeing that he had an ample share of knowledge. (TA.) [See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"frx","text_ar":"فرخ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in several places.] ―         -b3-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"War,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"battle;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the phrase,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahida Alr~awoEa","text_ar":"شَهِدَ الرَّوْعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He witnessed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was present at"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in, war,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"battle"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) [See also an ex. in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEafN","text_ar":"سَعَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n17080","headword_ar":"رُوعٌ","root":"rwE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heart:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part thereof which is the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawoE","text_ar":"رَوْع"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fear:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA:) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawaAd","text_ar":"سَوَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"core,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, * TA:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"understanding;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intellect."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawoEN","text_ar":"رَوْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in five places. You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqaEa *`lika fiY ruwEiY","text_ar":"وَقَعَ ذٰلِكَ فِى رُوعِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That came into my mind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, * TA.) And it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a Alr~uwHa nafava fiY ruwEiY","text_ar":"اـِنَّ الرُّوحَ نَفَثَ فِى رُوعِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily the Trusted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Trusty, Spirit"},{"kind":"text","text":"(meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Gabriel"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inspired into my mind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heart"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vaAbi ruwEuhu","text_ar":"ثَابِ رُوعُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went to"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. a mistake for"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing, and then returned to it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n17081","headword_ar":"رَوَعٌ","root":"rwE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality of exciting admiration and approval by beauty"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and pleasingness of aspect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by courage;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality denoted by the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arowaEu","text_ar":"اَرْوَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"applied to a man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rawoEaA='u","text_ar":"رَوْعَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"applied to a woman."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) [See also 1, near the end of the paragraph.]"}],"source_refs":["S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n17082","headword_ar":"رَوِعٌ","root":"rwE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAy^iEN","text_ar":"رَايِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; last sentence."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}